{"descriptions":[{"id":1361,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eSome volitional verbs have an imperative form. For instance:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཉན་\u003c/span\u003e becomes \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཉོན་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Listen!\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལང་\u003c/span\u003e becomes \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལོངས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Get up!\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThese forms are not used for the negative imperative, which instead takes the present-future form.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་ཉན།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Don\u0026rsquo;t listen.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་ཟ།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Don\u0026rsquo;t eat.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་ཡོང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Don\u0026rsquo;t come.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eHowever, there are many verbs that have no special form to denote the imperative. In such cases, the verb may be used by itself.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགསོལ་ཇ་མཆོད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Have some tea.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཕར་ཕེབས།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Go over there.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eIn most cases, the imperative (command) and optative (wish) moods are formed by using particles. The main particles are: \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདོ་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདང་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཨ་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཤིག་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཤོག་\u003c/span\u003e, and the construction \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརོགས་གནང་\u003c/span\u003e. These are discussed in the section on \u0026ldquo;imperative markers\u0026rdquo; below. (xxlink)\u003c/p\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:44 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:44 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}